function.arguments: {"@type":"application/tibls+json","itemListElement":[{"@type":"https://tibls.app/types/recipe","id":"5e6f7c8d-9b7f-4b5c-9c3e-2f7e8d9f6c7b","name":"Election Cake","summary":"A traditional yeast-risen cake with historical roots in colonial New England, known for its unique blend of spices and brandy-soaked fruits, topped with a simple glaze.","ingredients":[{"text":"2 packets active dry yeast (5½ tsp/14g)","sectionHeader":"Sponge"},{"text":"1½ cups (350ml) lukewarm water","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"1½ cups (210g) all-purpose flour","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"1½ cups (240g) seedless raisins, golden raisins, or currants (or any combination of the three)","sectionHeader":"Cake"},{"text":"¼ cup (60ml) brandy","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"1 cup (245g) all-purpose flour","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"½ tsp salt","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"2 tsp ground cinnamon","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"1 tsp ground nutmeg","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"½ tsp ground cloves","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"½ tsp ground ginger","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"¾ cup (170g) butter","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"1 cup (200g) granulated sugar","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"3 eggs, beaten","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"1 cup (115g) finely chopped pecans","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"2 tbsp whole milk","sectionHeader":"Glaze"},{"text":"1 tbsp butter, softened","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"½ tsp vanilla extract","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"1 cup (120g) powdered sugar","sectionHeader":""}],"steps":[{"text":"To create the sponge, sprinkle the yeast over the lukewarm water in a large bowl, before beating in the flour. Beat well until no lumps remain. Let stand in a warm place for 30 minutes while you continue. The sponge should bubble and increase in volume. Grease a 10-inch tube (25-cm) or Bundt pan with butter and dust with flour.","sectionHeader":"Sponge & Cake Method"},{"text":"In a small bowl, soak the dried fruit in the brandy. In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, and ginger.","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"In another large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in the beaten eggs until smooth.","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"Add the sponge to the creamed mixture. Beat very well.","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"Gradually add in the flour and spice mixture until smooth. Mix in the brandy, dried fruit, and chopped pecans.","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"Turn into the prepared pan, cover, and let rise in a warm place for about 3 hours, or until the batter rises to roughly an inch below the pan rim. Do not allow the batter to rise above the rim, as it may collapse in the oven.","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"Once risen, bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center can be removed cleanly. Let cool in the pan for 10 minutes before inverting onto a cooling rack to cool completely.","sectionHeader":""},{"text":"In a small saucepan over low heat, combine the milk and butter, stirring until the butter has melted.","sectionHeader":"Glaze Method"},{"text":"Gradually whisk in the powdered sugar until smooth and slightly thickened. Remove from the heat and whisk in the vanilla. Pour over the cooled cake.","sectionHeader":""}],"prepTime":210,"cookTime":45,"totalTime":255,"servings":10,"notes":[{"text":"Summary inferred from the historical context provided in the recipe."},{"text":"Time range of 35–45 minutes given; used 35 minutes for calculation."}]}]}
